Subject: Re: [T2] sandblast pushrod tubes?

Mike, I would just use a wire wheel on your grinder. I've used this for all
my con rods, my case studs, PR tubes in the past. It works fast and does a
good job. Don't spend money for anything fancy, I always have a 6: wire
wheel on one side of my grinder and it works great!!!
 
